729784f-a.title: Richmond: Tysen's Lane - Mill Road
729784f-a.text:
(1)
Tysens Lane, west side, 550 feet north of Mill
Road, showing the Lake-Tysen House. It dates in its
origin to the late seventeenth or early eighteenth
centuries. It is a fine example of Dutch Colonial
architecture.
May 2S, 192S
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(2)
A distant view of the house and adjoining barns,
seen from ill Road.
May 23, 1925
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTiONS
